Transcript: Raceman

33
00:01:00,703 --> 00:01:03,315
Adaptation: Ez, Keno83,
RonanaSplit & Lucile76

34
00:01:04,823 --> 00:01:06,363
www. forom. com

35
00:01:16,943 --> 00:01:17,779
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

36
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:19,480
Stevie caught me sneaking out
of the bunkhouse.

37
00:01:19,481 --> 00:01:20,901
The current's moving north.

38
00:01:22,039 --> 00:01:23,851
If we leave now, we could be home
by morning.

39
00:01:23,852 --> 00:01:25,132
Who wants to go home?

40
00:01:25,885 --> 00:01:26,737
Me.

41
00:01:28,780 --> 00:01:29,834
I hate this place.

42
00:01:30,570 --> 00:01:31,326
I feel like a prisoner.

43
00:01:31,327 --> 00:01:32,210
Oh, come on.

44
00:01:32,211 --> 00:01:35,300
It's just temporary until the sheriff says
we're ready to go back.

45
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:36,555
Back for what?

46
00:01:37,409 --> 00:01:39,611
They keep telling us how special we are

47
00:01:40,264 --> 00:01:41,524
and how we have to function as a team.

48
00:01:41,525 --> 00:01:42,847
A team for what?

49
00:01:44,066 --> 00:01:45,223
What is the big plan?

50
00:01:45,224 --> 00:01:46,174
Survival.

51
00:01:54,443 --> 00:01:55,155
But if our bodies...

52
00:01:56,393 --> 00:01:58,629
if they really are different...

53
00:01:58,630 --> 00:02:00,191
uh-huh, they are.

54
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:03,658
Then there has to be a purpose.

55
00:02:04,432 --> 00:02:06,240
Why won't they tell us our purpose?

56
00:02:08,352 --> 00:02:09,178
What the hell do you think you're doing?

57
00:02:09,179 --> 00:02:11,449
Damn you, stevie, you got no right
tellin' us what to do.

58
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:13,440
They aren't my rules, Derek,
they're szura's!

59
00:02:13,441 --> 00:02:14,649
Szura's in charge!

60
00:02:14,991 --> 00:02:17,268
Whatever he says goes-

61
00:02:22,102 --> 00:02:24,533
- What'd you do that for?
- 'Cause I'm tired of this crap.

62
00:02:25,037 --> 00:02:26,529
He look's bad, chris.

63
00:02:26,530 --> 00:02:27,534
It's his fault.

64
00:02:27,535 --> 00:02:28,805
Dumb ass.

65
00:02:30,564 --> 00:02:32,350
Someone's been telling me
what to do all my life.

66
00:02:33,297 --> 00:02:35,969
No more. No more.

67
00:02:36,553 --> 00:02:37,688
I'm gettin' out of here.

68
00:02:40,049 --> 00:02:41,168
Chris, wait for me.

69
00:02:41,169 --> 00:02:42,792
Wait for me, chris!

70
00:02:57,069 --> 00:02:59,229
Were you just planning on never talking
to me again?

71
00:03:00,085 --> 00:03:00,633
Kira...

72
00:03:00,634 --> 00:03:02,769
I called you ten times tonight.

73
00:03:03,623 --> 00:03:04,729
I know. I'm sorry.

74
00:03:05,110 --> 00:03:07,952
I just-things are kinda crazy right now.

75
00:03:08,515 --> 00:03:11,087
Crazy because my father told you
to stay away from me?

76
00:03:13,671 --> 00:03:15,229
I just came from the water, lewis.

77
00:03:16,885 --> 00:03:18,203
I almost went in.

78
00:03:18,837 --> 00:03:20,001
I still may.

79
00:03:21,027 --> 00:03:22,559
I don't think
you oughta do that.

80
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,356
Why not?

81
00:03:23,849 --> 00:03:26,210
What is this big secret
that everybody's keeping?

82
00:03:27,244 --> 00:03:29,562
You, my dad, my stepmother,

83
00:03:29,563 --> 00:03:31,419
you all went into the water
and came out different.

84
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,655
Yeah, but I don't think
that's such a good thing.

85
00:03:34,792 --> 00:03:35,991
It kinda messed me up.

86
00:03:35,992 --> 00:03:37,796
But it's something that you share...

87
00:03:39,143 --> 00:03:41,534
that you all share together
that makes you closer.

88
00:03:43,645 --> 00:03:45,265
I just want to know what that feels like.

89
00:03:46,497 --> 00:03:48,256
Will you come in the water with me?

90
00:03:49,302 --> 00:03:51,762
And you can just watch
and let me know what happens.

91
00:03:52,729 --> 00:03:53,411
No.

92
00:03:54,496 --> 00:03:56,314
But I want it so bad, lewis.

93
00:03:58,275 --> 00:04:02,243
I just don't want to do it alone. Please.

94
00:04:06,846 --> 00:04:08,141
Please.

95
00:04:10,162 --> 00:04:10,835
I can't.

96
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:12,794
I'm sorry, kira.

97
00:04:15,699 --> 00:04:16,572
You're not my friend.

98
00:04:21,466 --> 00:04:22,852
You're not my friend!

99
00:04:48,225 --> 00:04:48,977
Daddy?

100
00:04:50,365 --> 00:04:52,034
Hey, what are you doing up?

101
00:04:52,738 --> 00:04:53,841
I couldn't sleep.

102
00:04:54,526 --> 00:04:55,740
What are you doing?

103
00:04:56,555 --> 00:04:57,357
Nothing.

104
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,629
Are you looking for monsters?

105
00:05:00,231 --> 00:05:01,093
No, honey.

106
00:05:01,094 --> 00:05:02,271
There's no monsters.

107
00:05:03,236 --> 00:05:04,531
It's okay. I'm not afraid,

108
00:05:05,679 --> 00:05:07,718
as long as they stay in the water.

109
00:05:11,197 --> 00:05:13,029
I offered to put her to bed,
but she wanted you.

110
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:13,967
Oh, it's okay.

111
00:05:14,752 --> 00:05:15,484
Hey, dad,

112
00:05:16,439 --> 00:05:17,720
if I'm gonna be living here full-time now,

113
00:05:17,721 --> 00:05:19,675
can I get a phone in my room, like at mom's?

114
00:05:20,107 --> 00:05:22,148
Uh, you know what?
Can we talk about this in a second?

115
00:05:24,087 --> 00:05:24,728
All right.

116
00:05:25,162 --> 00:05:26,099
Do you brush your teeth?

117
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:26,724
Yep.

118
00:05:26,725 --> 00:05:28,870
All right. Say good night to your brother.

119
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:31,842
- Night, Jess!
- Night, Rose!

120
00:05:33,493 --> 00:05:36,244
- Good night, Rosie.
- Good night, Larkin.

121
00:05:38,686 --> 00:05:39,767
Can we call mommy?

122
00:05:41,030 --> 00:05:44,130
Um, you know, I think she's still at work.

123
00:05:45,357 --> 00:05:46,499
I miss her.

124
00:05:46,817 --> 00:05:48,711
Ohh, I know, honey.

125
00:05:50,251 --> 00:05:52,700
I liked it better when I lived at her house,
too,

126
00:05:53,898 --> 00:05:55,133
when we shared.

127
00:05:57,364 --> 00:05:59,836
Why doesn't she want us there anymore, dad?

128
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,081
She does.

129
00:06:01,552 --> 00:06:02,838
She loves you very much.

130
00:06:05,392 --> 00:06:06,787
Then why aren't we there?

131
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,437
I have to tell them the truth.

132
00:06:10,636 --> 00:06:12,307
I can't keep dodging
their questions.

133
00:06:13,311 --> 00:06:14,178
They miss their mother.

134
00:06:14,179 --> 00:06:15,963
They don't understand why they're not with her anymore.

135
00:06:17,551 --> 00:06:18,584
Well, what can you say?

136
00:06:19,944 --> 00:06:21,725
"Sorry, kids, but mom has been cloned

137
00:06:21,726 --> 00:06:22,638
"by alien light creatures,

138
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:24,062
think she might try to kill you"?

139
00:06:25,410 --> 00:06:26,130
I don't know.

140
00:06:27,217 --> 00:06:28,964
Maybe I could just tell them that she's sick.

141
00:06:31,046 --> 00:06:32,151
You know, she...

142
00:06:32,996 --> 00:06:34,657
she got infected by something.

143
00:06:34,658 --> 00:06:36,381
I think that would just scare them.

144
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:39,782
I think the truth would scare them even more.

145
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:42,553
Yeah, well, we don't even know what the truth is.

146
00:06:45,663 --> 00:06:46,317
You know...

147
00:06:47,876 --> 00:06:48,823
Mariel's a doctor.

148
00:06:48,824 --> 00:06:51,198
Has she ever run any tests on herself?

149
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,278
I don't know.

150
00:06:53,132 --> 00:06:55,302
I think you should insist that she have some tests run

151
00:06:55,883 --> 00:06:58,101
so we can at least know what we're dealing with here.

152
00:06:58,102 --> 00:06:59,280
Where, at the hospital?

153
00:06:59,652 --> 00:07:00,806
That'll raise too many questions.

154
00:07:02,448 --> 00:07:03,503
You could have her come to your station.

155
00:07:03,504 --> 00:07:04,496
You could do it.

156
00:07:05,984 --> 00:07:07,380
You wouldn't have a problem with that?

157
00:07:07,931 --> 00:07:14,454
Oh, honey. It's okay. I've accepted my new jean size,

158
00:07:15,157 --> 00:07:17,106
and I'm feeling much more secure.

159
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:20,573
You can hang out with your ex-wife as long as you want to,

160
00:07:21,276 --> 00:07:23,578
just so long as you come home to me.

161
00:07:29,465 --> 00:07:30,278
And me.

162
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:48,988
Excuse me. Hey, baby.

163
00:07:49,692 --> 00:07:50,727
No breakfast?

164
00:07:51,592 --> 00:07:52,710
Nobody called me.

165
00:07:52,711 --> 00:07:55,911
Well, we don't usually hand out formal invitations.

166
00:07:56,163 --> 00:07:57,654
You know, you pop down to the kitchen, pull up a-

167
00:07:57,655 --> 00:07:59,599
you told lewis not to talk to me anymore, didn't you?

168
00:08:00,424 --> 00:08:02,524
No, I-I mentioned that you were 17.

169
00:08:03,018 --> 00:08:04,393
I'm not looking to date him, dad,

170
00:08:05,579 --> 00:08:07,201
and I don't really think that's the issue, anyway.

171
00:08:07,202 --> 00:08:08,733
I mean, Derek was my age,

172
00:08:08,987 --> 00:08:10,096
and as soon as he came back from the water,

173
00:08:10,097 --> 00:08:12,871
you told him to stay away from me. Why?

174
00:08:12,872 --> 00:08:14,108
Because I knew...

175
00:08:16,321 --> 00:08:17,555
he'd never be right for you.

176
00:08:18,207 --> 00:08:21,428
Because he'd been changed, like you, like Mariel,

177
00:08:21,429 --> 00:08:22,934
like half this town, for all I know.

178
00:08:22,935 --> 00:08:23,843
Kira, kira.

179
00:08:24,688 --> 00:08:26,048
You are perfect the way you are.

180
00:08:26,049 --> 00:08:27,742
No, I'm not.

181
00:08:31,323 --> 00:08:32,580
Kira, come here.

182
00:08:32,581 --> 00:08:34,124
Russell, I can't come there now.

183
00:08:35,149 --> 00:08:36,463
Because I'm on my way to work.

184
00:08:37,630 --> 00:08:40,117
I understand the kids have questions, but-

185
00:08:40,118 --> 00:08:41,524
kira, wait, I want to talk to you.

186
00:08:41,525 --> 00:08:42,502
Of course I care.

187
00:08:43,196 --> 00:08:43,603
I'm just-

188
00:08:43,604 --> 00:08:45,769
listen-Mariel, would you talk to her, please? Kira!

189
00:10:00,770 --> 00:10:01,501
Derek.

190
00:10:01,774 --> 00:10:03,251
Well, hey, there, girlfriend.

191
00:10:04,066 --> 00:10:04,907
What's up?

192
00:10:05,632 --> 00:10:08,247
Christina, this is kira.

193
00:10:10,506 --> 00:10:12,910
oh, this is gonna be fun.

194
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:25,261
There's no sign of her out here, lewis.

195
00:10:25,262 --> 00:10:27,571
Check logan's bay and I'm gonna head up the coast a bit,

196
00:10:27,572 --> 00:10:29,165
then I'll meet you back at the station, all right?

197
00:10:29,739 --> 00:10:30,897
roger that, sir.

198
00:10:31,738 --> 00:10:33,349
the sheriff is your daddy?

199
00:10:33,687 --> 00:10:35,190
Oh, if I'd have known you were banging her,

200
00:10:35,191 --> 00:10:36,858
I would have gotten us off that island a week ago.

201
00:10:36,859 --> 00:10:37,579
Yeah, right.

202
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:39,255
Ooh, could I borrow your hoodie?

203
00:10:40,447 --> 00:10:41,253
Where have you been?

204
00:10:42,310 --> 00:10:44,428
Uh... just away.

205
00:10:45,184 --> 00:10:46,046
Away where?

206
00:10:47,034 --> 00:10:48,684
Derek was a bad boy and your daddy sent him

207
00:10:48,685 --> 00:10:51,453
to devil's island, and that's where he met me.

208
00:10:52,459 --> 00:10:53,250
And who are you?

209
00:10:54,199 --> 00:10:54,803
Christina.

210
00:10:54,804 --> 00:10:57,028
He calls me "Chrissie. "
Isn't that sweet?

211
00:10:58,648 --> 00:11:00,545
So what were you doing in the water, daddy's girl?

212
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:02,123
My name's kira.

213
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:03,740
Okay.

214
00:11:05,241 --> 00:11:06,716
I wanted to know what was out there.

215
00:11:07,589 --> 00:11:08,654
Besides us?

216
00:11:09,821 --> 00:11:12,589
- You got a car?
- Yeah.

217
00:11:12,590 --> 00:11:13,418
Where?

218
00:11:14,645 --> 00:11:15,187
Up there.

219
00:11:15,971 --> 00:11:17,288
I didn't want my dad to know I was here.

220
00:11:19,041 --> 00:11:20,103
Good thinking.

221
00:11:21,352 --> 00:11:23,001
Well, kira...

222
00:11:24,841 --> 00:11:25,914
we could use a ride,

223
00:11:26,306 --> 00:11:27,859
and you look like you could use some fun.

224
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:30,701
Um, yeah, we-we can't go anywhere with her.

225
00:11:30,702 --> 00:11:31,439
Why not?

226
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:33,725
Uh, because if her dad finds out-

227
00:11:33,726 --> 00:11:35,470
and what is he gonna do, arrest us?

228
00:11:35,922 --> 00:11:38,177
Not if he wants to keep his little operation on the downlow.

229
00:11:38,178 --> 00:11:40,121
But he could send us back, chris.

230
00:11:41,098 --> 00:11:42,020
Maybe not...

231
00:11:42,885 --> 00:11:44,834
not if we have kira here to protect us.

232
00:11:46,544 --> 00:11:48,160
You really want to know what "different" means?

233
00:11:51,568 --> 00:11:52,320
Yes.

234
00:11:52,793 --> 00:11:54,109
Then stick with us.

235
00:11:54,641 --> 00:11:55,584
We'll give you the whole show.

236
00:11:57,758 --> 00:11:59,067
Derek, we could use some clothes.

237
00:11:59,068 --> 00:12:00,504
How about you take us girls shopping?

238
00:12:00,515 --> 00:12:03,686
What do you think, kira, little shop-a-thon to kick the day off?

239
00:12:05,172 --> 00:12:05,688
All right.

240
00:12:05,689 --> 00:12:08,572
All right! Two hungry shoppers, ready to roll.

241
00:12:29,015 --> 00:12:29,713
I, um...

242
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,342
I called the hospital and told them
that I'd be in after lunch.

243
00:12:34,785 --> 00:12:35,944
I thought about what you said on the phone,

244
00:12:35,945 --> 00:12:37,838
and maybe this is a good idea.

245
00:12:38,201 --> 00:12:39,508
I'm glad you changed your mind.

246
00:12:40,452 --> 00:12:41,416
What do you want to do?

247
00:12:43,276 --> 00:12:45,042
Well, I think we should start with blood work.

248
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:46,979
I know when jesse was at the hospital,

249
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:49,049
there was some confusion in the lab about your blood.

250
00:12:49,050 --> 00:12:50,696
Mm-hmm, well, there's no confusion now.

251
00:12:50,697 --> 00:12:51,966
It's definitely changed.

252
00:12:53,536 --> 00:12:55,394
It has much higher levels of hemoglobin.

253
00:12:56,539 --> 00:12:58,790
I think that's why I can stay underwater for so long.

254
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:00,950
I didn't know that you could.

255
00:13:01,684 --> 00:13:03,834
But none of this is really what you're concerned about, is it?

256
00:13:05,252 --> 00:13:07,105
You want to know if there's something inside me

257
00:13:07,106 --> 00:13:08,410
that's gonna hurt our kids.

258
00:13:08,411 --> 00:13:10,153
I just think we owe them an explanation

259
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:12,631
as to why they're not with you anymore,

260
00:13:12,632 --> 00:13:14,305
and since we don't have all the answers yet...

261
00:13:14,622 --> 00:13:17,167
I don't want them to be afraid of me, russell.

262
00:13:17,168 --> 00:13:18,739
Are you afraid of what we'll find?

263
00:13:20,118 --> 00:13:20,869
M aybe.

264
00:13:28,176 --> 00:13:29,481
What is that?

265
00:13:31,130 --> 00:13:33,822
That is part of one of the light creatures from the water.

